<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n13107i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n13" href="#n13107i">N13 (VI.D.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n13all.htm#n13107i"> 107(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> in rage become an / avatar</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;And it was then that Cuchulain&apos;s first distortion came on, and <mark>he was filled with swelling</mark> and great fulness, like breath in a bladder, until he became a terrible, fearful, many-coloured, wonderful Tuaig, and he <mark>became as big as a Fomor</mark>, or a man of the sea, the great and valiant champion, in perfect height over Ferdiad. <small> Douglas Hyde, <a name="SEGL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SEGL"><cite title="source">The Story of Early Gaelic Literature</cite></a> (1920) 78</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05046i" href="c5all.htm#c05046i">VI.C.05:046(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
